benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: DELETE /1.0/kb/invoiceItems/{invoiceItemId}/customFields - Remove custom fields from invoice item

covered: Valid Deletion: All TC01 and TC02 cover successful deletion scenarios, including removal of all fields and specific field removals.
Non-Existent Resource: TC08 covers 404 when invoice item does not exist.
Missing/Invalid Input Handling: TC07 covers invalid UUID; TC10 covers malformed customField parameter; TC18 covers duplicates; TC11 covers extra/unexpected parameters.

Authorization/Headers: TC09 covers missing required header; TC06 covers only required header; TC19 covers invalid/expired token; TC05 covers additional header usage; TC16 covers header length handling.
Service Availability: TC14 covers 503/service unavailable scenario.
Negative/Edge Cases: TC03 (one field), TC04 (no fields), TC15 (injection attempt), TC17 (mixed valid/invalid IDs), TC20 (header parsing regression).
Bulk/Stress-like Scenarios: TC12 (100+ IDs) and TC13 (heavy load) simulate large/degraded conditions.
gaps: Concurrency/Race Conditions: No explicit test for concurrent deletions or race conditions when multiple clients attempt to modify the same resource.
Soft Deletes: No explicit test confirming whether items are soft-deleted vs hard-deleted or any auditing implications.
Pagination: Not applicable to DELETE with fields, but guidelines mention pagination for large datasets; no dedicated pagination test is provided (not strictly required for this endpoint).
Caching Behavior: No tests validating caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) or caching invalidation semantics.
Rate Limiting: No tests validating behavior under burst requests or throttling constraints.
recommendations: Add a concurrency/race-condition scenario to ensure safe handling when multiple clients delete or modify the same invoice item custom fields concurrently.
Introduce a soft-delete vs hard-delete clarification test if applicable to the API semantics, including auditing/visibility checks.
Include tests around caching headers and validation of caching-related responses if the endpoint participates in caching (ETag, Cache-Control).
Add rate-limiting/throttling tests to verify API behavior under high request volume and ensure proper error/throttle responses.
Consider a dedicated test for a scenario combining multiple edge cases (e.g., valid IDs with duplicates and extra parameters) to validate stability under complex inputs.
